    meaningReversed: 'Self-doubt, weakness, insecurity, or abuse of power. You may be lacking confidence in your abilities or conversely, using force where gentleness would serve better. This reversal can indicate that fear has gained the upper hand, that you\'re avoiding confrontation when courage is needed, or that you\'re suppressing rather than integrating difficult emotions. It may suggest raw emotion overwhelming reason, or letting your "inner beast" run wild without the tempering influence of wisdom. Alternatively, this card reversed can point to being too passive, allowing others to walk over you, or losing touch with your personal power. You might be doubting your capacity to handle challenging situations or people. Sometimes this reversal indicates misusing strength - being controlling, aggressive, or domineering rather than persuasive and patient. Reconnect with your inner courage, practice self-compassion, and remember that true strength is gentle but unwavering.',
    description: 'A serene figure in flowing white robes adorned with flowers reaches down with infinite gentleness to close the jaws of a golden lion, the king of beasts. Above their head floats the infinity symbol, the lemniscate of eternal spirit, showing that this power comes from an inexhaustible source beyond the physical realm. The figure wears a crown of blossoms, representing the beauty that flourishes when force is tempered by compassion. Mountains rise in the distant background, but the scene is bathed in peaceful warmth. The lion - symbol of raw passion, primal instinct, and untamed nature - does not resist or struggle. Instead, it yields willingly to the gentle hands upon its muzzle, recognizing a power greater than brute force. This is not domination through violence but transformation through love. The figure shows no fear, no aggression, only calm confidence and tender strength. Flowers bloom around them, evidence that gentleness creates the conditions for life to flourish. This card teaches that the strongest among us are those who can be gentle, that true courage faces fears with an open heart, and that love is the most powerful force in the universe.',
